column4: <content>Which can also be seen in sixteenth cent[ury] illustrations, for instance in Virgil Solis' engraving (pl. II). Later on it becomes the subsidiary motif to pig-[onleesbaar] (e.g. in E[tienne] Delaune's print of 1560 or in [Adriaen] Collaert's roundel after Hans Bol, pl. 7b).</content>
